<span id="freeTextContainer6849305520562325243"><br/>This review is sooooooooo late...as are many of the others that are going to follow in the next few weeks. Living out in the booonies- sometimes my internet doesn&apos;t work with me. Sorry NetGalley. :(<br/><br/>Blue Ridge, North Carolina-<br/><br/><span>[image error]</span><img src='https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1468271452i/19685838.jpg' alt=' photo 07caee29-3541-4559-b440-53889d6e23fe_zps39jy2uss.jpg' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/><br/>Becca Eckersley- a law school student from a prominent family escapes to her families vacation home on school break...but as soon as she arrives, her past catches up with her...In the place she felt safest- she is brutally murdered. It is obvious to the detectiv</span>
