<div id="review_1430505071" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1430505071" />
    <a title="Linda Strong" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/13684015-linda-strong"><img alt="Linda Strong" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1452733337p2/13684015.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1430505071?book_show_action=true">Nov 01, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Linda Strong" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Linda Strong" href="/user/show/13684015-linda-strong">Linda Strong</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="ebook 9781496700995" href="/book/show/25488865-summit-lake">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/13684015-linda-strong?shelf=netgalley">netgalley</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/13684015-linda-strong?shelf=read-in-2015">read-in-2015</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1430505071" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3536879055251408498">Lake Summit is a small town in the Blue Ridge Mountains.<br/><br/>Lake Summit is where a young woman is brutally assaulted and strangled in her home.<br/><br/>Lake Summit is where Kelsey Castle, a crime reporter, is sent to cover the story.<br/><br/>This is the first time ever that a murder has been committed in this tight-knit community. The local police have been replaced by the State Police. The State Police aren&apos;t talking to anyone. The town is buzzing with all kinds of theories.<br/><br/>When Kelsey starts asking questions, she f</span>
  <span id="freeText3536879055251408498" style="display:none">Lake Summit is a small town in the Blue Ridge Mountains.<br /><br />Lake Summit is where a young woman is brutally assaulted and strangled in her home.<br /><br />Lake Summit is where Kelsey Castle, a crime reporter, is sent to cover the story.<br /><br />This is the first time ever that a murder has been committed in this tight-knit community. The local police have been replaced by the State Police. The State Police aren't talking to anyone. The town is buzzing with all kinds of theories.<br /><br />When Kelsey starts asking questions, she faces a wall of silence. Cops won't talk to her. The autopsy report is not on file. There are no available medical records. The family won't talk to her. So what is everyone hiding?<br /><br />The book bounces back and forth between a year before Becca Eckersley died and what's happening currently with Kelsey's investigation. The past is filled with secrets and lies that Kelsey is trying to untangle.<br /><br />The author has done a fantastic job of keeping the suspense at a high level of tension. I absolutely could not put this one down. I read until my eye sight got blurry. This is a new author to me, but one I'm sure we will all hear a lot more about down the road.<br /><br />I just can't say enough about this book. Well-written ... seamlessly merging the past into present day. There are a lot of characters, and all of them are unforgettable. And watch out for the twists and turns here and there. Just when I thought I had it figured out, the author would push me into a new direction.<br /><br />Highly recommend for anyone who likes a good who-done-it! 5 Stars.<br /><br />My thanks to the author / Kensington Books / Kensington/ NetGalley who furnished a digital copy in exchange for an honest, unbiased review.</span>
  <a data-text-id="3536879055251408498" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


