<span id="freeTextContainer3795158411894390284">What a read this was Charlie Donlea BRAVO for writing a compelling believable thriller that kept my attention from the very first page i think this author will go places &amp; hope this book will be a series but who knows!!<br/><br/>Kelsey Castle was a writer &amp; getting over her demons after time out her boss Penn Courtney sends her to Summit Lake to investigate the murder of Becca Eccersley has been found murdered her father is a lawyer &amp; wants to be a judge &amp; he wants the perp found.<br/><br/>She is a uni student stud</span>
  <span id="freeText3795158411894390284" style="display:none">What a read this was Charlie Donlea BRAVO for writing a compelling believable thriller that kept my attention from the very first page i think this author will go places &amp; hope this book will be a series but who knows!!<br /><br />Kelsey Castle was a writer &amp; getting over her demons after time out her boss Penn Courtney sends her to Summit Lake to investigate the murder of Becca Eccersley has been found murdered her father is a lawyer &amp; wants to be a judge &amp; he wants the perp found.<br /><br />She is a uni student studying law &amp; her friends jack, Brad, Gail hang out all the time when they find out Becca has been murdered they find out that Becca is not what she seems, even though she is close to Brad Stays at his house till early hours then leaves she is in love with Jack so both fight for her affections until Brad finds a secret out about Becca &amp; Jack that she wants to keep secret.<br /><br /><br />Becca keeps a journal that keeps her thoughts &amp; secrets in so in comes Detective Madison to investigate who killed Becca what he finds is that Becca was promiscuous &amp; liked attention by the opposite sex what happens from here is a rollercoaster ride in the lives of Jack Brad &amp; Gail that may ruin their friendship forever.<br /><br />I loved this book &amp; thought Summit Lake had a certain aura about it which is a place anyone could live in tranquil &amp; peaceful a 5 for Mr Donlea an author to watch out for. </span>
